The latest checkpoint was therefore approximately 111.7 MB of serialized replacement history, almost entirely inline image URLs. The rollout is not recursively embedding prior `replacement_history` objects. It is append-only snapshot amplification: each compaction persists another full snapshot containing the same surviving media.

