### Reproduction

I inspected another long-lived image-heavy thread after a local compaction-v2 checkpoint. Sanitized structural measurements from the latest `compacted.payload.replacement_history`:

| Metric | Observed value |
| --- | ---: |
| Rollout JSONL size | 2,873,784,216 bytes |
| Compaction records | 54 |
| Replacement-history items | 211 |
| User messages | 209 |
| Retained `input_image` parts | 142 |
| Retained image detail | 142 × `high` |
| Retained inline image/data-URL characters | 111,563,732 |
| Retained text characters | 56,733 |
| Effective model context window | 353,400 tokens (`gpt-5.6-sol`) |

The token sequence makes the impact visible:

1. Immediately after compaction, local recomputation emitted `total_tokens=294,141`, `input_tokens=0`, which rendered as 17% context remaining.
2. The first real post-compaction model response reported `input_tokens=342,406`, `output_tokens=230`, `total_tokens=342,636`, which rendered as 3% remaining.

The apparent drop was not caused by the file-read output displayed immediately before the second token event. That usage belongs to the request that generated the read call, so the result could not yet have been part of its input. The first server-provided usage corrected the lower-bound local estimate for the already-installed image-heavy prompt.

No raw rollout is attached because it contains private prompts, paths, tool output, and images. The counts above were computed structurally without printing content.

All 142 retained images in this reproduction were already surrounded by the canonical local-image text wrapper: an opening `<image ... path="...">` item immediately before the `InputImage` and a closing `</image>` immediately after it. The compactor can therefore remove the inline bytes without losing the model-callable source path.

### Current upstream source analysis

Current upstream `main` now uses a 64k retained-message budget, but the budget remains text-only:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/compact_remote_v2.rs#L52-L54

`build_v2_compacted_history` selects retained user/developer/system messages from the compaction prompt and passes them through the retained-message truncator:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/compact_remote_v2.rs#L443-L460

The truncator charges only text. `InputImage` and `InputAudio` contribute zero, and the partial-message path always preserves them:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/compact_remote_v2.rs#L482-L560

The current tests explicitly lock in this behavior by asserting that images survive truncation and that an image-only message costs only the `.max(1)` message floor:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/compact_remote_v2.rs#L729-L819

Local-image prompt construction already emits the source path in an adjacent model-visible wrapper and keeps the raw image as a separate content item:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/protocol/src/models.rs#L1392-L1400

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/protocol/src/models.rs#L1568-L1588

`view_image` already accepts a model-generated path plus an optional environment ID and resolves it through the selected environment filesystem:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/tools/handlers/view_image.rs#L53-L57

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/tools/handlers/view_image.rs#L118-L168

There is already a content-aware image estimator elsewhere in core. It replaces inline base64 payload size with an estimated model-visible image cost (approximately 1,844 tokens for ordinary resized images, with separate original-detail patch accounting):

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/context_manager/history.rs#L521-L579

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/context_manager/history.rs#L652-L679

That estimator is used after history replacement for the provisional token-count event, but not for retained-message selection. `recompute_token_usage` also estimates only base instructions plus installed history and marks the result as `input_tokens=0`, explainin
g why the first real server count can jump materially:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/session/mod.rs#L3668-L3704

Historic rollouts currently receive no equivalent cleanup. Reconstruction selects the latest surviving `replacement_history` as its base and installs it exactly before replaying the suffix:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/session/rollout_reconstruction.rs#L113-L185

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/session/rollout_reconstruction.rs#L317-L345

Both resume and fork use the shared reconstruction path. It currently prepares legacy media in memory while explicitly leaving the recorded rollout unchanged, so image-heavy checkpoints remain active and are processed again on every reconstruction:

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/session/mod.rs#L1248-L1333

https://github.com/openai/codex/blob/0fb559f0f6e231a88ac02ea002d3ecd248e2b515/codex-rs/core/src/session/mod.rs#L1345-L1370

